question_stem.en:
Results of a recent study on the association between levels of glycosylated hemoglobin (HbA1c) and levels of high-sensitivity C-reactive protein (hs-CRP) in patients with type II diabetes mellitus (T2DM) read as follows:

"The results of our study show that levels of HbA1c positively correlated with the levels of hs-CRP (r = 0.80). The probability that these results were due to chance alone is 3%, with a 10% chance of concluding no relationship between HbA1c and hs-CRP when one truly exists." {{exhibit_1}}

Based on this information, which of the following most likely represents the *p*-value and the power of the correlation test in the study?

question_stem.zh:
一项关于 II 型糖尿病 (T2DM) 患者糖化血红蛋白 (HbA1c) 水平与高敏 C 反应蛋白 (hs-CRP) 水平之间关联性的最新研究结果如下：

“我们的研究结果表明，HbA1c 水平与 hs-CRP 水平呈正相关 (r = 0.80)。 这些结果仅由偶然性造成的概率为 3%，而当 HbA1c 和 hs-CRP 之间确实存在关系时，得出它们之间没有关系的概率为 10%。” {{exhibit_1}}

基于此信息，以下哪项最有可能代表该研究中相关性检验的 *p* 值和效能？
